author: Sam Morshead For Mailonline
title: Burnley vs Lincoln City, FA Cup fifth round, LIVE | Daily Mail Online
text:
12:26 Imps fans in fine voice 
'In getting here, they've been brilliant and out-performed Championship teams. In their minds, every outcome is possible,' says Michael Owen on BT Sport. 
Around 3,000 Lincoln fans are belting out some Imps classics. They're still dreaming. Will they be come 3pm? 
Let's find out. Lincoln City fans in the stands show their support 12:25 Here we go then... 
It's almost kick-off time in Burnley. Lincoln have dumped out Oldham, they've dumped out Ipswich, they've dumped out Brighton. Now they've got one of the Premier League's best sides when it comes to home record. 
The Cowley brothers have their work cut out this afternoon. Lincoln City players warm up prior to kick off A Lincoln City fan in the stand wearing face paint 12:15 
And the excitement is building at Turf Moor. Can Lincoln spring yet another surprise? A Lincoln City fan before the match 12:05 Team news from Turf Moor 
Burnley: Heaton, Darikwa, Keane, Tarkowski, Flanagan, Westwood, Barton, Gudmundsson, Gray, Vokes, Arfield 
Subs: Robinson, Barnes, Lowton, Ward, Boyd, Mee, Agyei 
Lincoln: Farman, Wood, Waterfall, Raggett, Habergham, Arnold, Woodyard, Power, Hawkridge, Rhead, Muldoon 
Subs: Marriott, Long, Walton, McMenemy, McCoombe, Southwell, Ward 11:41
